  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-08-25",
    "date": "2021-01-21T15:00:52Z",
    "text": "Campus Free Speech Restoration Act\n\nThis bill generally prohibits public institutions of higher education (IHEs) that participate in federal student-aid programs from restricting noncommercial expressive activities (e.g., peacefully assembling, distributing literature, or carrying signs) on campus. It also requires private IHEs that receive federal funds to provide students with their policies related to expressive rights."
